WEBVTT

00:01.681 --> 00:03.415
You wrote about me and Tank?

00:03.441 --> 00:06.596
You had no right without
asking my permission.

00:09.264 --> 00:11.880
- I would never try to replace your mom.
- She's still alive.

00:11.912 --> 00:13.464
Regina: Her name is Hope Paxton.

00:13.584 --> 00:15.282
I booked a ticket to Atlanta.

00:15.401 --> 00:16.433
I'm coming with you.

00:16.469 --> 00:17.398
Daphne: Is that your son?

00:17.436 --> 00:19.269
He's with my son-of-a-bitch ex-husband...

00:19.305 --> 00:20.319
Wherever he is.

00:20.358 --> 00:24.256
I kissed someone in Mexico,
but it didn't mean anything.

00:24.273 --> 00:25.805
Was it with that audiologist guy?

00:25.805 --> 00:26.889
- Quinn?
- Yeah.

00:26.921 --> 00:28.245
- I'm pregnant.
- Well, is it mine?

00:28.280 --> 00:30.189
- Yes.
- You said you were into somebody else.

00:30.210 --> 00:31.336
I was faithful to you.

00:31.390 --> 00:33.566
You don't think every
single person in this country

00:33.587 --> 00:35.544
doesn't write off an
extra thing here or there?

00:35.664 --> 00:38.028
Do you really want our
kids to hear you say that?

00:38.057 --> 00:40.433
That cheating is okay
'cause everyone else does it?

00:40.458 --> 00:41.991
I didn't think of it as cheating.

00:43.175 --> 00:45.917
Wait. Okay. Is the IRS
coming after you guys?

00:45.930 --> 00:47.229
Could you guys go to jail?

00:47.246 --> 00:49.582
No one's going to jail, okay?

00:49.610 --> 00:51.837
But you have to sell the car washes.

00:51.850 --> 00:54.234
Yes. That'll take some of the pressure off.

00:54.388 --> 00:55.966
Is there anything I can do?

00:56.086 --> 00:57.541
No, you're already paying rent,

00:57.576 --> 01:00.366
which we don't like, but
we appreciate. We just...

01:00.869 --> 01:02.419
we wanted you guys to know.

01:03.349 --> 01:04.717
I've been thinking about

01:04.908 --> 01:06.466
maybe taking a semester off?

01:06.482 --> 01:07.933
No. Absolutely not.

01:07.953 --> 01:10.545
Honey, your education is our priority.

01:10.574 --> 01:12.037
We will continue to support you.

01:12.069 --> 01:13.207
And I can help.

01:13.242 --> 01:15.083
John: And we appreciate that, but truly,

01:15.203 --> 01:16.814
things are stabilizing.

01:16.860 --> 01:20.570
We're not gonna allow our
situation to impact anybody.

01:20.574 --> 01:23.154
We just... we didn't
want it to be a secret.

01:23.224 --> 01:25.885
- So there's nothing we can do to help?
- No.

01:26.005 --> 01:29.996
Listen, everything is gonna
work out just fine, okay?

01:30.469 --> 01:31.881
You can count on that.

01:33.680 --> 01:36.251
I can't believe our parents are broke.

01:36.289 --> 01:39.637
- Hey, they're not broke.
- They're just not part of the 1% anymore.

01:39.757 --> 01:41.237
I feel kind of guilty.

01:41.453 --> 01:43.302
I'm the one they bailed out last year.

01:43.344 --> 01:45.496
Yeah, but you've only been
around for a few years.

01:45.524 --> 01:46.958
Think about me and Toby.

01:47.078 --> 01:49.571
If they didn't have to
pay for art supplies,

01:49.595 --> 01:52.011
and Buckner, and music equipment...

01:52.081 --> 01:53.884
Yeah, they could own
their own island by now.

01:54.175 --> 01:55.737
They're still paying my tuition,

01:55.766 --> 01:58.201
so I better go make it worth their pain.

01:58.205 --> 01:59.385
I'll see you guys later.

02:01.716 --> 02:02.438
Toby: Oh.

02:02.497 --> 02:03.726
Is that your hammer girl?

02:03.992 --> 02:05.634
Hi! Sorry. Excuse me,

02:05.754 --> 02:07.467
could I just see your shirt?

02:09.814 --> 02:10.664
Toby: Oh, man.

02:10.914 --> 02:13.145
You know what that says, right?

02:13.448 --> 02:16.535
Like, you didn't accidentally
fall into that shirt.

02:16.569 --> 02:17.640
What do you mean?

02:17.981 --> 02:19.514
Can I ask you where you bought that?

02:19.593 --> 02:21.758
Yeah. It's this site
called Tramp Stamp Teaze.

02:21.794 --> 02:23.465
That's "Teaze" like a slutty girl.

02:23.515 --> 02:25.544
Also "T's," like T-shirt. Get it?

02:25.596 --> 02:27.267
- Got it.
- Yeah. It's clever.

02:27.280 --> 02:28.277
It's really, really clever.

02:28.327 --> 02:30.059
- Cool. Thanks.
- Mm-hmm.

02:31.371 --> 02:33.382
- Wow.
- Did you see that?

02:33.639 --> 02:34.549
(Scoffs)

02:35.060 --> 02:36.288
Yeah. I saw it.

02:36.315 --> 02:39.459
My empowered, take-no-prisoners
hammer girl just became

02:39.495 --> 02:43.480
a stupid, slutty... (Groans)

02:43.515 --> 02:45.101
Hammered girl.

02:47.711 --> 02:48.965
(Groans)

02:50.360 --> 02:55.351
- synced and corrected by chamallow -
- www.addic7ed.com -

02:57.652 --> 02:59.576
So what is it? What's the big news?

02:59.643 --> 03:02.331
I talked with our people
on the ground in San Marcos.

03:02.568 --> 03:05.837
Ramón's sign language
class is up to 12 students.

03:05.896 --> 03:07.150
No way!

03:07.200 --> 03:08.479
Guess who one of them is?

03:08.882 --> 03:11.462
A certain 15-year-old named Pati.

03:11.773 --> 03:13.020
Seriously?

03:13.398 --> 03:14.989
I told you she was gonna show.

03:14.993 --> 03:16.380
You totally did!

03:16.432 --> 03:19.383
I'm so happy right now. You have no idea.

03:19.451 --> 03:21.658
They said if more people
could get themselves there,

03:21.704 --> 03:23.889
then the class would
probably double in size.

03:24.009 --> 03:25.530
Pati had the same issue.

03:27.321 --> 03:29.278
The bus we took from her house cost what?

03:29.302 --> 03:31.380
Two pesos? What's that in dollars?

03:31.384 --> 03:33.084
Around 13 cents.

03:33.163 --> 03:37.446
That means a yearly bus
pass costs about $50.

03:37.469 --> 03:39.548
So, for $600,

03:39.565 --> 03:41.204
12 more people could learn how to sign?

03:41.443 --> 03:43.140
Uh-oh. I know that look.

03:43.458 --> 03:45.589
I could totally raise $600.

03:46.873 --> 03:48.178
If anyone could...

03:51.181 --> 03:53.928
Uh, I gotta go, but I'll see what I can do.

03:54.140 --> 03:55.302
Enjoy Guatemala.

03:55.337 --> 03:56.433
Talk to you later.

03:56.591 --> 03:57.471
Bye.

03:57.505 --> 03:58.299
Come in.

04:00.135 --> 04:01.258
What's up?

04:01.480 --> 04:03.458
Hi! Hey.

04:04.853 --> 04:07.251
You know that girl Pati I told you about?

04:07.516 --> 04:09.311
She showed up in sign language class.

04:09.318 --> 04:10.484
That's awesome.

04:10.519 --> 04:12.910
They have about 12 students right now,

04:12.976 --> 04:14.548
but they could double that.

04:14.627 --> 04:15.599
If...

04:15.719 --> 04:18.735
How do you feel about raising $600

04:18.765 --> 04:20.159
to buy bus passes

04:20.173 --> 04:22.279
for a bunch of deaf kids in Mexico?

04:22.341 --> 04:25.769
Uh, I feel great about that?

04:25.889 --> 04:28.237
- (Laughs)
- Perfect answer.

04:31.233 --> 04:33.290
Eric: Anyway, I think
this is close to all of it.

04:33.846 --> 04:35.459
I guess I live here now.

04:35.719 --> 04:37.157
How does it feel?

04:38.702 --> 04:39.724
Like home.

04:39.844 --> 04:41.240
Aww.

04:41.785 --> 04:43.961
I'm glad Daphne is cool with us being here.

04:44.081 --> 04:46.436
I imagine it's kind of a big deal for her.

04:52.031 --> 04:54.004
- She's upset.
- No.

04:54.183 --> 04:54.889
But?

04:55.454 --> 04:57.402
There's something I need to tell you.

04:58.042 --> 05:00.032
Remember that dinner she made for us

05:00.115 --> 05:01.815
and I got so upset?

05:01.844 --> 05:02.808
Yeah.

05:02.821 --> 05:05.106
She started questioning me a lot...

05:06.008 --> 05:07.724
And she knew I was lying,

05:07.782 --> 05:09.515
- so...
- No, you didn't.

05:09.635 --> 05:10.874
I had to.

05:11.326 --> 05:13.178
Did you tell Bay? And John and Kathryn?

05:13.226 --> 05:15.589
- No, no, no, no. Just Daphne.
- (Sighs)

05:16.524 --> 05:19.698
Look, she knows me so
well, and I was wrestling

05:19.748 --> 05:21.178
with whether or not to move in with you

05:21.215 --> 05:23.390
and I felt like I had to tell someone.

05:26.870 --> 05:28.199
Are you really mad?

05:30.098 --> 05:31.299
I guess it's done.

05:31.818 --> 05:35.352
And you have nothing to
worry about. I promise.

05:38.106 --> 05:39.105
Okay.

