05:50.907 --> 05:54.823
All I need is for 60
people to give me $10 each.

05:56.458 --> 05:57.835
- Me, too.
- Thanks.

05:57.955 --> 06:00.192
If we have any extra, I'm gonna use it

06:00.235 --> 06:03.222
to buy sign language
dictionaries and flashcards.

06:07.906 --> 06:10.971
I really want to do this on my own.

06:12.747 --> 06:16.512
Oh, my god. It's even more
disgusting than I imagined.

06:19.042 --> 06:21.472
"Don't worry, I'm on the pill,"

06:22.106 --> 06:24.701
"number one walk of shame champion,"

06:24.736 --> 06:26.553
"my kitty's Brazilian."

06:26.673 --> 06:27.804
Yikes.

06:28.955 --> 06:33.484
Ho ho, get a girl drunk enough
and you can push her into sex.

06:33.484 --> 06:36.257
Yeah, that's a great message
to be sending the world.

06:36.621 --> 06:39.207
Who's making these things anyway?

06:39.716 --> 06:42.001
Let's see.

06:43.455 --> 06:44.818
Bay: Hmm.

06:45.722 --> 06:48.059
I think I've seen that guy around campus.

06:48.288 --> 06:50.937
- Wait, he's a student?
- I'm pretty sure.

06:51.923 --> 06:53.518
I will go pay him a visit.

06:54.171 --> 06:55.265
I got this.

06:59.807 --> 07:02.715
Oh. Wow, that was a good kick.

07:04.548 --> 07:05.878
Yeah. Yeah.

07:08.080 --> 07:09.347
(Lily and Julian laugh)

07:09.389 --> 07:12.075
- (Laughs)
- It's the strangest feeling.

07:12.822 --> 07:14.173
Hey, babe.

07:14.599 --> 07:16.307
Oh! Hey.

07:17.663 --> 07:19.257
You must be Julian.

07:19.667 --> 07:21.137
I'm Toby.

07:23.215 --> 07:25.406
Oh, thank you.

07:32.543 --> 07:34.101
Absolutely.

07:44.550 --> 07:45.662
Oh, thank you.

07:45.698 --> 07:46.986
Sure.

07:47.973 --> 07:49.442
So...

07:49.692 --> 07:51.271
does he stop by often?

07:52.133 --> 07:53.192
No.

07:55.961 --> 07:57.676
Toby, he works in the deaf program.

07:57.703 --> 07:58.883
We're gonna cross paths.

08:00.698 --> 08:01.582
Right.

08:01.867 --> 08:03.434
(Phone vibrates)

08:03.554 --> 08:05.318
(Vibrating continues)

08:06.013 --> 08:06.990
It's your mom.

08:07.166 --> 08:08.538
(Sighs)

08:08.573 --> 08:10.190
That's like, her fifth phone call today.

08:12.447 --> 08:13.440
Everything okay?

08:14.165 --> 08:14.757
Yeah...

08:14.877 --> 08:15.947
Actually, there...

08:15.957 --> 08:18.147
there is something I've been
meaning to discuss with you.

08:19.760 --> 08:20.657
Okay.

08:23.455 --> 08:25.541
My parents want me to think about...

08:27.292 --> 08:28.405
moving home.

08:30.798 --> 08:31.493
To London.

08:33.589 --> 08:34.802
Why would we do that?

08:35.245 --> 08:36.669
So they could help us.

08:36.979 --> 08:39.153
But my family is here,

08:39.565 --> 08:41.847
my job is here, your job is here.

08:42.828 --> 08:46.355
But my parents have experience
raising a special needs child.

08:46.588 --> 08:48.236
I was thinking just in the beginning,

08:48.269 --> 08:49.879
maybe the first few years.

08:50.037 --> 08:52.307
- Years?
- My parents have a whole community out there.

08:52.367 --> 08:54.790
They know the best doctors,
the best therapists.

08:54.910 --> 08:56.303
They've done this before.

08:56.502 --> 08:58.859
Not just literally, but emotionally,

08:59.048 --> 09:00.131
they're prepared.

09:01.376 --> 09:03.315
We are having this child.

09:03.355 --> 09:04.323
They are not.

09:04.646 --> 09:06.992
All I ask is that you keep an open mind.

09:07.022 --> 09:08.810
It's something we should talk about.

09:10.501 --> 09:12.805
We could build a really
great life in London.

09:18.505 --> 09:20.337
John: So is her mind already made up?

09:20.679 --> 09:21.341
No,

09:21.653 --> 09:24.302
but I feel like she's
leaning in that direction.

09:24.422 --> 09:26.197
Do you want to move to London?

09:26.453 --> 09:27.211
No.

09:27.394 --> 09:29.242
I don't know anyone there and

09:29.458 --> 09:30.980
I don't even know if I can get a work visa.

09:31.262 --> 09:32.172
John: Okay then.

09:32.409 --> 09:33.752
We gotta convince her to stay.

09:33.909 --> 09:35.689
You know we'll do whatever we can.

09:36.082 --> 09:38.198
I think she needs to see
that there's more people here

09:38.212 --> 09:40.780
that she can count on besides just me.

09:40.816 --> 09:42.861
Well, then invite her
over for dinner tonight.

09:42.884 --> 09:43.974
We'll rally around her.

09:44.047 --> 09:44.951
John: Absolutely.

09:45.071 --> 09:47.513
We missed out on so many years with Daphne.

09:47.533 --> 09:49.670
We cannot let that happen
with our grandchild.

09:50.985 --> 09:51.825
Thanks.

09:54.920 --> 09:57.114
If I could have a moment of your time...

09:58.311 --> 09:59.418
Sir, just a few dollars,

09:59.438 --> 10:01.583
you could give someone
the gift of language!

10:02.336 --> 10:03.579
Hi, guys! Di...

10:05.357 --> 10:06.238
(Sighs)

10:06.673 --> 10:08.146
Uh-huh. Yeah.

10:08.477 --> 10:10.801
All right. Thank you so much,
man. I really appreciate it.

10:11.044 --> 10:12.060
Yeah. I'll see you soon.

10:12.467 --> 10:13.313
(Exhales)

10:13.348 --> 10:16.098
- Who was that?
- (Laughs) We are having a...

10:16.122 --> 10:18.635
Okay, I don't know how to say "fundraiser,"

10:18.655 --> 10:20.802
but... fundraiser at Scratch tonight!

10:20.962 --> 10:22.021
What do you mean?

10:22.057 --> 10:23.717
My buddy is a bartender there.

10:23.723 --> 10:25.342
He says he'll let us pass around a hat,

10:25.369 --> 10:27.629
put up signs, whatever we want.

10:27.918 --> 10:28.945
That's amazing!

10:28.980 --> 10:31.249
Yeah! I'll send an e-mail
blast, invite everyone I know.

10:31.262 --> 10:33.998
And I'll post this at the dorm
and the disabilities office.

10:34.002 --> 10:35.768
Hey, do you think I should...

10:35.804 --> 10:37.871
give like, a little presentation?

10:37.991 --> 10:39.216
Absolutely.

10:39.276 --> 10:40.907
Those people see what you saw,

10:41.027 --> 10:42.675
they're gonna bury you in cash.

10:44.729 --> 10:46.360
- You are the best.
- Hold on.

10:46.615 --> 10:49.218
You don't even know the best part yet.

10:49.258 --> 10:52.489
It's... I don't know how
to say this either, um...

10:53.320 --> 10:55.235
(Imitates a gun)

10:55.623 --> 10:56.879
- Cowboys?
- Yeah!

10:56.959 --> 10:58.458
Country Western night.

10:58.528 --> 11:00.960
You know. Line dancing,
boots, hats, the whole thing.

11:01.416 --> 11:02.536
Seriously?

11:02.552 --> 11:03.748
Hey, who cares, right?

11:03.825 --> 11:04.931
I guess.

11:05.051 --> 11:06.432
Yee-haw!

11:07.899 --> 11:09.531
Like cowboys say.

11:12.878 --> 11:13.705
Heyo!

11:14.158 --> 11:16.192
Oh, there they are!

11:16.232 --> 11:19.194
Oh, look at that belly!

11:19.550 --> 11:21.836
- Doesn't she look amazing?
- Hi.

11:21.956 --> 11:24.030
Oh, it's so good to see you.

11:24.052 --> 11:25.622
It's been too long.

11:25.648 --> 11:26.865
It's good to see you, too.

11:26.951 --> 11:28.516
Oh, hello in there.

11:28.533 --> 11:29.939
This is your grandpa.

11:30.125 --> 11:33.226
I cannot wait to take you
to your first Royals game.

11:33.875 --> 11:37.325
And you and I are going to bake
and draw and have sleepovers,

11:37.335 --> 11:39.252
and I am going to spoil you rotten!

11:39.295 --> 11:40.159
John: Yeah.

11:40.176 --> 11:41.927
Okay, everybody inside. Come on!

11:41.950 --> 11:43.463
Oh, yeah. Come on!

11:45.002 --> 11:47.904
You know, there are some
terrific places for kids

11:47.913 --> 11:50.157
with special needs right
here in Kansas City?

11:50.336 --> 11:52.327
Kathryn has done all this great research.

11:52.414 --> 11:53.996
Oh. That's really nice of you.

11:54.607 --> 11:57.469
Yeah. We are happy to do
whatever you need us to do.

11:57.482 --> 11:59.539
We want to be a big
part of your baby's life.

12:00.892 --> 12:01.769
You told them.

12:02.424 --> 12:03.677
It's their grandchild.

12:05.193 --> 12:08.206
- I just feel ambushed.
- No, no, no, no.

12:08.208 --> 12:10.096
We just want to talk it through.

12:10.098 --> 12:11.881
We know how much you love your job here,

12:11.912 --> 12:13.522
and you're so good at it...

12:14.067 --> 12:16.207
But London is where my family lives

12:16.218 --> 12:18.861
and they have experience
raising a special needs child.

12:18.913 --> 12:20.347
John: And we respect that.

12:20.467 --> 12:22.345
But you know, Kathryn and
I learned sign language

12:22.382 --> 12:24.205
when Daphne came into our lives.

12:24.381 --> 12:26.651
We are more than willing
to do whatever it takes

12:26.671 --> 12:28.863
to help raise a child with Down syndrome.

12:33.004 --> 12:37.184
You know, I pulled some of
Bay and Toby's old baby things.

12:37.230 --> 12:39.370
- Do you want to go look at them?
- Sure. Thanks.

12:45.633 --> 12:47.533
Oh, look!

12:47.569 --> 12:48.635
That's adorable.

12:49.814 --> 12:52.484
I used to put Toby to bed after a long day

12:52.540 --> 12:56.041
and still be sad that I didn't
get to see him till the morning.

12:56.394 --> 12:57.819
I can't wait.

13:01.610 --> 13:03.467
It goes by so fast.

13:05.070 --> 13:06.035
You'll see.

13:06.071 --> 13:08.036
(Sighs) I already feel like that.

13:08.156 --> 13:11.257
I'm more than halfway and there's
just so many decisions to make.

13:12.880 --> 13:14.961
Is there anything I can do to help?

13:16.425 --> 13:18.064
My mom wants me to go home,

13:18.099 --> 13:20.333
Toby wants me to stay here, and...

13:20.724 --> 13:22.869
And now I'm worried that I'm
being unfair to you and John.

13:27.375 --> 13:30.877
You do what you think
is best for your baby.

13:32.003 --> 13:33.898
The rest of us will fall in line.

13:35.583 --> 13:37.500
I want to be with my family.

13:38.470 --> 13:39.852
I want to go home.

13:46.445 --> 13:48.410
(Country music playing)

13:57.338 --> 13:59.303
Hi! Thank you for coming!

14:02.041 --> 14:03.943
